
Local Copy of the Code : git clone https://github.com/matplotlib/matplotlib.git

Updating the code : Do retreive the latest code after regular intervals using:

cd matplotlib
git pull

The tree in matplotlib will now have the latest changes.

Steps to contribute code:

Create an account on GitHub.
Fork the project repository: click on the 'Fork' button near the top of the page, to create a separate copy for yourelf.

Clone this to your device:
git clone https://github.com/<YOUR GITHUB USERNAME>/matplotlib.git

Enter the directory and install the local version of Matplotlib.

Create a branch to hold your changes:
git checkout -b my-feature origin/main
and start making changes. Never work in the main branch!

Work on this copy on your device, and after you're done:

git add lib/matplotlib/collections.py
git commit (Assuming collections.py was edited)

to record your changes in Git, then push them to GitHub with:
git push -u origin my-feature
